[% # Standard Template Toolkit header for AI Guidelines
   # File: root/Documentation/AI_Guidelines.tt
   # Purpose: Guidelines for AI-assisted development in the Comserv system
   # Last Updated: 2025-09-22
   # Version: 2.0.1
%]
[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/AI_Guidelines.tt,v 2.1 2025/09/22 shanta Exp shanta - AI Guidelines' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="documentation-container">
    <h1>AI Development Guidelines</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated">
        Last Updated: [% USE date; date.format(date.now, '%Y-%m-%d') %] | 
        Version: 2.1
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
        <h2>About This Document</h2>
        <p>This guideline is for both developers and AI assistants. It aims to help navigate the complexities of using AI assistants in development, including choosing the right tool for the job, understanding limitations, and ensuring best practices are followed. All documentation is maintained in <code>.tt</code> files for browser-friendly viewing. <code>.md</code> files are used as a staging area for AI assistants and review before changes are applied to <code>.tt</code> files.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
        <h2>Documentation File Types</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>.tt files:</strong> Official, browser-friendly documentation. All published documentation should be in <code>.tt</code> files.</li>
            <li><strong>.md files:</strong> Used primarily for AI assistants (e.g., Zencoder) that require Markdown. These files serve as a staging area for edits and reviews before changes are applied to <code>.tt</code> files.</li>
            <li><strong>Workflow:</strong> Make changes in the <code>.md</code> file, review them, then copy the approved content to the corresponding <code>.tt</code> file for publication.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
        <h2>Glossary</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Session:</strong> The entire process to get code changes done, tracked in <code>current_session.md</code>. May last many days and covers all related issues.</li>
            <li><strong>Chat:</strong> Each conversation between developer and AI (may be called differently by each assistant). For example, in GitHub Copilot, a chat refers to the interaction window where prompts and responses occur.</li>
            <li><strong>Prompt:</strong> An exchange between the developer and the AI within a chat. Prompts are the individual questions or commands given to the AI.</li>
            <li><strong>System:</strong> A group of code performing a function (e.g., file management system).</li>
            <li><strong>GPT-4.1:</strong> The default AI model used for general-purpose tasks, including documentation, coding, and multi-step processes. It is highly capable and context-aware.</li>
            <li><strong>GPT-0:</strong> A lightweight AI model optimized for quick, simple tasks with minimal resource usage. Best for straightforward operations.</li>
            <li><strong>5 Miny:</strong> A specialized AI model designed for rapid, time-sensitive tasks. It prioritizes speed over deep context understanding.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
        <h2>AI Assistant Comparison</h2>
        <table class="standard-table">
            <tr>
                <th>Assistant</th>
                <th>Strengths</th>
                <th>Limitations</th>
                <th>Best For</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>GitHub Copilot</td>
                <td>Code completion, multi-language support</td>
                <td>May generate generic code, context limits</td>
                <td>General coding, boilerplate</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Cascade</td>
                <td>Good at refactoring, context awareness</td>
                <td>Cannot edit untracked files</td>
                <td>Refactoring, code review</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Zencoder</td>
                <td>Fast, concise suggestions</td>
                <td>Short prompt window, loses context</td>
                <td>Quick fixes, small changes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>OllamAssist</td>
                <td>Open-source, customizable</td>
                <td>Requires local server</td>
                <td>Custom workflows</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>ProxyAI</td>
                <td>Acts as an intermediary for AI tasks, handles complex workflows, provides <code>+-</code> diffs for code and documentation changes</td>
                <td>Cannot directly access files or codebase, relies on explicit input. Limited to the active file in the IDE and cannot read multiple files for context or duplication detection.</td>
                <td>Generating prompts for other assistants, documentation updates, and task coordination</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <h3>GitHub Copilot Details</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Chat:</strong> Refers to the interaction window where developers and the AI exchange prompts and responses.</li>
            <li><strong>Edit:</strong> The process of modifying code or documentation based on developer instructions. GitHub Copilot excels at inline code suggestions and edits.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
        <h2>Choosing the Right Assistant</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>For documentation, guidelines, and complex multi-step tasks: <strong>GitHub copilot</strong> (or GPT-4) is recommended.</li>
            <li>For code refactoring and context-aware changes: <strong>Cascade</strong>.</li>
            <li>For quick, small code changes: <strong>Zencoder</strong>.</li>
            <li>For custom workflows and open-source needs: <strong>OllamAssist</strong> (if installed).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="reminder-box">
        <h2>Guideline Maintenance</h2>
        <p>Update this guideline as new assistants are added or existing ones change. All sub-guidelines and documentation should inherit from this primary document.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <h2>⚠️ IMPORTANT: File Modification Guidelines</h2>
        <p><strong>WARNING TO ALL AI ASSISTANTS</strong>: Always modify existing files instead of creating new ones when possible. Only create new files when absolutely necessary and with explicit approval. Never modify existing files without explicit user confirmation.</p>
    </div>

