    <section id="guideline-maintenance" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Guideline Maintenance</h2>
        <p>Update this guideline as new assistants are added or existing ones change. All sub-guidelines and documentation should inherit from this primary document.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="file-management" class="doc-section">
        <h2>File Management</h2>

        <h3>Modification Policy</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Always prefer modifying existing files</strong> over creating new ones</li>
            <li>New files should only be created when:
                <ul>
                    <li>Adding completely new functionality that doesn't fit in existing files or will make the exiting file to large. the sugest which sub could be refracted into other file.</li>
                    <li>Following the project's architectural patterns (e.g., new controllers, models, utils etc.)</li>
                    <li>Those explicitly requested by the user</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Always create backups before making changes. These should be done by the user with the file manager system</li>
            <li>Document all changes in the appropriate changelog</li>
            <li>Keep the codebase clean and organized</li>
            <li>New files should added to the Primary documentation file for the system</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Naming Conventions</h3>
        <table class="standard-table">
            <tr>
                <th>File Type</th>
                <th>Naming Convention</th>
                <th>Example</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Controller</td>
                <td>PascalCase.pm</td>
                <td>Documentation.pm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Template</td>
                <td>snake_case.tt</td>
                <td>user_profile.tt</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Test File use the browser to do this or the catalyst testing system.</td>
                <td>descriptive_name.t</td>
                <td>documentation_controller.t</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
       <h3>If the name of a file is changed make sure it is refactored in all files that use the old naming.</h3>
    </section>

    <section id="code-standards" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Code Standards</h2>

        <h3>Logging</h3>
        <p>Always use structured logging with context:</p>
        <pre><code class="perl">$self->logging->log_with_details(
    $c,                    # Catalyst context
    'info',                # Log level (debug, info, warn, error)
    __FILE__,              # File name
    __LINE__,              # Line number
    'method_name',         # Method or section name
    "Descriptive message"  # Clear, actionable message
);</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section id="workflow" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Development Workflow</h2>

        <h3>Adding New Features</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Identify the problem or feature to be added</li>
            <li>Read all existing documentation to see what was in place and that it matches the current state of the code.</li>
            <li>Research and gather information</li>
            <li>Design the solution</li>
            <li>Implement the solution</li>
            <li>Check for existing implementations that can be extended</li>
            <li>Modify the appropriate controller, model etc or create new files sub only if absolutely necessary</li>
            <li>Update or add templates as needed</li>
            <li>Update routes if needed especially if new sub .tt are created.</li>
            <li>Add tests only in the catalyst system or via the browser. </li>
            <li>Record all session events in the current_session.md so we know what is happening in each prompt. Help tune the guidelines to over come problems.</li>
            <li>Update the documentation</li>
        </ol>
            <li>Update documentation</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section id="documentation" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Documentation</h2>

        <h3>Code Comments</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Document the "why" not just the "what" and "how"</li>
            <li>Keep Documentation up to date with code changes</li>
            <li>Fallow the documentation guidelines.</li>
            <li>Reference related issues or documentation.</li>
            <li>Make sure all files relating to the system are in the documentation.</li>
            <li>Use consistent formatting</li>
            <li>Reference related issues or documentation</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="troubleshooting" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

        <h3>Common Issues</h3>
        <dl>
            <dt>Mismatched file/package names</dt>
            <dd>Verify case sensitivity matches exactly</dd>

            <dt>Missing dependencies</dt>
            <dd>Check <code>cpanfile</code> and <code>Makefile.PL</code></dd>

            <dt>Template errors</dt>
            <dd>Look for unclosed tags or syntax errors</dd>
        </dl>
    </section>

    <section id="ai-integration" class="doc-section">
        <h2>AI Integration</h2>

        <h3>Resource Management</h3>
        <p><strong>All AI assistants must adhere to these resource guidelines:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Operation Limits</strong>: 15-20 operations per conversation</li>
            <li><strong>Prompt Limit</strong>: 3 prompts maximum before mandatory handoff</li>
            <li><strong>Session Tracking</strong>: All session events must be recorded in current_session.md</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>File Editing Protocol</h3>
        <p>When editing Template Toolkit (.tt) files:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Check if a corresponding .md file exists</li>
            <li>If not, create one: <code>cp target_file.tt target_file.md</code></li>
            <li>Edit the .md file with proper Template Toolkit structure</li>
            <li>Present the command to apply changes: <code>cp target_file.md target_file.tt</code></li>
            <li>Let the user execute the final copy command</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Template Structure</h3>
        <p>All .md files must include proper Template Toolkit structure:</p>
        <pre><code>[% META title = 'Descriptive Page Title' %]
[% PageVersion = 'path/to/file.tt,v 1.0 YYYY/MM/DD author Exp' %]

<!-- HTML content here -->
[% IF condition %]
    <div>Conditional content</div>
[% END %]</code></pre>

        <h3>Resource Conservation</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Minimize shell command usage</li>
            <li>Avoid redundant file operations</li>
            <li>Combine operations where possible</li>
            <li>Focus only on essential tasks</li>
            <li>Stop before hitting limits to prevent lockouts</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="usage-instructions" class="doc-section">
        <h2>Usage Instructions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Code Editing</strong>:
                <ol>
                    <li>Provide context about the file or code section to be modified.</li>
                    <li>ProxyAI will generate a <code>+-</code> diff showing the exact changes:
                        <pre><code>- Old code to be removed
+ New code to be added</code></pre>
                    </li>
                    <li>Review the diff in the IDE plugin interface, with highlighted changes for clarity.</li>
                    <li>Make any necessary adjustments to the code directly in the diff view.</li>
                    <li>Click <code>Add AI_Guidelines.tt</code> to insert the changes at the cursor location or a specified block.</li>
                    <li>Click <code>Apply</code> to confirm and apply the modifications.</li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Documentation Updates</strong>:
                <ol>
                    <li>Provide explicit input about the documentation to be updated.</li>
                    <li>ProxyAI will generate a <code>+-</code> diff showing the exact changes:
                        <pre><code>- Old documentation to be removed
+ New documentation to be added</code></pre>
                    </li>
                    <li>Review the diff in the IDE plugin interface, with highlighted changes for clarity.</li>
                    <li>Make any necessary adjustments to the documentation directly in the diff view.</li>
                    <li>Click <code>Add AI_Guidelines.tt</code> to insert the changes at the cursor location or a specified block.</li>
                    <li>Click <code>Apply</code> to confirm and apply the modifications.</li>
                </ol>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>

[% # Include any necessary JavaScript or additional template components %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    <div class="debug-footer">
        <h3>Template Debug Info</h3>
        <p>Template: [% template.name %]</p>
        <p>Roles: [% c.user.roles.join(', ') %]</p>
    </div>
[% END %]